descript.abstract: The footprint of a building designed for a function or to afford a particular convenience or service. These are a subset of the buildings found in the BuildingFootprint feature class and only those actively managed by a local government, or other land holder. The information typically comes from design drawings of the facilities and is a framework for the management of interior spaces and work activities associated with such.

attr.attrdef: Internal feature number.

attrdomv.udom: Sequential unique whole numbers that are automatically generated.

attr.attrdef: Feature geometry.
A classification of the access allowed to the interior space
The total area of the building
The type of building occupancy
Locally assigned Building Identifier
The condition of the building
Foreign key to locally assigned Facility Site Identifier
The total floor count for the building
The user who performed the last update
The date the feature was last updated in the maintenance database
The full name of the building
Indicates which organization maintains the building
The date the building was opened for operations
The hours of operation for the building
Indicates which organization owns the building
The short, or abbreviated, name or number of the building
Length of feature in internal units.

attrdomv.udom: Positive real numbers that are automatically generated.

attr.attrdef: Area of feature in internal units squared.

attrdomv.udom: Positive real numbers that are automatically generated.

attr.attrdef: The height of the building
